comments: Antetokounmpo (MIL) cleanly blocks Durant's (BKN) jump shot attempt.
Holiday (MIL) legally contests Irving's (BKN) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Green (BKN) and Middleton (MIL) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Griffin (BKN) delivers body contact to Holiday (MIL) as he cuts back toward the rim and affects the driving shot attempt.
Middleton (MIL) and Holiday (MIL) make incidental contact with Griffin (BKN) as they each attempt to gain control of the loose ball.
Tucker (MIL) is moving forward when marginal contact occurs with Durant's (BKN) lower half as he secures the rebound.
DiVincenzo (MIL) legally contests Irving's (BKN) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.

Griffin (BKN) brushes Antetokounmpo's (MIL) right arm during his upward shooting motion and marginal contact occurs. Griffin slightly extends his right foot simultaneously and marginal contact occurs with Antetokounmpo's right leg.
Tucker (MIL) swipes forward and marginal contact occurs with Irving's (BKN) left arm at the end of the drive.

Antetokounmpo (MIL) is drifting toward Irving (BKN) slightly when marginal body contact occurs during Irving's upward shooting motion. Simultaneously, Tucker (MIL) rests his hand on Irving's right side and marginal contact occurs.
Holiday (MIL) and Durant (BKN) make incidental body contact with one another as Durant secures the rebound.
Irving (BKN) engages and disengages with Holiday (MIL) during rebounding.
Harris (BKN) firms up in his screening position in Tucker's (MIL) path and absorbs the contact.
DiVincenzo (MIL) legally contests Durant's (BKN) jump shot attempt.

Irving (BKN) makes clean contact with the ball as marginal contact occurs with Middleton's (MIL) backside simultaneously. Middleton then legally goes into the backcourt to retrieve the ball after it is deflected away.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) extends his hand forward and marginal contact occurs with Irving's (BKN) side as Irving is already losing balance.
Durant (BKN) and Tucker (MIL) engage during the inbound and when Durant stops and releases from the contact, Tucker's momentum carries him backwards.
Tucker (MIL) legally contests Durant's (BKN) jump shot attempt.
